{"author":{"id":"69a73b59e8bca0653e9174a374f9f55c998c9a49750b37bad6bd3960e96b7ca3"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1633532452,"nonce":"trsCkyYZM8ZVC84uh6XPkTxkxY8=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDODBZtRc430RVf","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/788#issuecomment-936449375"},"message":"@TheChymera First of all, there's no reason to do `setup.py build`, as `setup.py install` runs it anyway.  More importantly, `setup.py install` is deprecated; you should install with `pip install .` instead.  In my personal projects, I take the policy (not that it's ever come up) that if things break with `setup.py install` but work with `pip install`, then the problem is that you're using `setup.py install`.","files":null}]}